17/09/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan met with US Ambassador Eric Edelman on Tuesday (16 September) to discuss Washington's request for peacekeeping troops in Iraq. Afterwards, Edelman told reporters that the Bush administration respects Ankara's decision-making process and realises that it requires time. The two officials also discussed economic, political and social reforms Turkey must undertake to increase its chances of EU membership. (Hurriyet - 17/09/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 16/09/03)
